                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Class="mb-2">Step 1: Create Your Master Password</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-3">
                        On first launch, you'll be prompted to create a master password. This password encrypts your API keys
                        using AES-256-GCM encryption and stores them locally in your browser's storage.
                        <strong>Important:</strong> Your password is never sent to any server, and there is no password recovery option.
                        If you forget it, you'll need to reset the app (losing all saved API keys).
                    </MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-4" Color="Color.Secondary">
                        üí° <strong>Tip:</strong> Choose a password you can remember, but make it strong. Consider using a password manager.
                    </MudText>

                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Class="mb-2">Step 2: Choose Your TTS Providers</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-3">
                        Stitch supports 7 TTS engines (5 cloud + 2 offline). You have two options:
                    </MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-2">
                        <strong>Option A: Use Cloud Providers (Best Quality)</strong><br/>
                        Navigate to <MudLink Href="apikeys"><strong>API Keys</strong></MudLink> and add credentials for at least one provider:
                    </MudText>
                    <ul class="mb-3">
                        <li><strong>Google Cloud TTS</strong> - Best balance of quality and cost ($0.000016/char for Neural2)</li>
                        <li><strong>ElevenLabs</strong> - Most natural voices, great for audiobooks (free tier: 10,000 chars/month)</li>
                        <li><strong>Deepgram Aura</strong> - Ultra-low latency (&lt;200ms), ideal for real-time apps</li>
                        <li><strong>Azure Cognitive Services</strong> - 100+ languages, excellent multilingual support</li>
                        <li><strong>Amazon Polly</strong> - 100+ voices, multiple engine types (Standard, Neural, Long-form, Generative)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-2">
                        <strong>Option B: Use Offline TTS (No Internet Required)</strong><br/>
                        No API keys needed! Use the built-in offline engines:
                    </MudText>
                    <ul class="mb-4">
                        <li><strong>Piper TTS</strong> - High-quality neural voices (50+ languages). Download models from <MudLink Href="offline">Offline Mode</MudLink> page.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-4" Color="Color.Secondary">
                        üí° <strong>Tip:</strong> You can use both! Set up cloud providers for premium quality, and download offline models for when you don't have internet.
                    </MudText>

                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Class="mb-2">Step 3: Add Your API Keys (Cloud Providers Only)</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-3">
                        For each cloud provider you want to use, click the <strong>"Add Key"</strong> button on the API Keys page.
                        See the <strong>Provider Setup Guides</strong> section below for step-by-step instructions on obtaining API keys.
                        After entering a key, use the <strong>"Test Connection"</strong> button to verify it works.
                    </MudText>

                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Class="mb-2">Step 4: Start Synthesizing Speech</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-3">
                        Go to the <MudLink Href=""><strong>Home</strong></MudLink> page and follow these steps:
                    </MudText>
                    <ol class="mb-3">
                        <li>Enter or paste your text in the text area (up to 100,000 characters)</li>
                        <li>Select a <strong>TTS Provider</strong> from the dropdown</li>
                        <li>Choose a <strong>Voice</strong> - use filters to narrow down by language, gender, or accent</li>
                        <li>Adjust <strong>Speed</strong>, <strong>Pitch</strong>, and <strong>Volume</strong> if desired (optional)</li>
                        <li>Click <strong>"Synthesize Speech"</strong></li>
                        <li>Wait for synthesis to complete, then <strong>Play</strong> or <strong>Download</strong> your audio</li>
                    </ol>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-4" Color="Color.Secondary">
                        üí° <strong>Tip:</strong> The estimated cost is shown in real-time as you type. Long text is automatically split into chunks for processing.
                    </MudText>

                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Class="mb-2">Step 5: Upload Files (Optional)</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-3">
                        Want to convert a PDF or text file to speech? Use the <MudLink Href="file-upload"><strong>File Upload</strong></MudLink> page:
                    </MudText>
                    <ol class="mb-3">
                        <li>Drag and drop a PDF (up to 100 MB) or text file (up to 50 MB)</li>
                        <li>The app extracts text automatically and detects chapters (if applicable)</li>
                        <li>Review and edit the extracted text if needed</li>
                        <li>Select your provider and voice</li>
                        <li>Click <strong>"Continue to Synthesize"</strong> to transfer the text to the Home page</li>
                    </ol>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-4" Color="Color.Secondary">
                        üí° <strong>Tip:</strong> For scanned PDFs, the app will warn you that OCR (Optical Character Recognition) may be needed for better text extraction.
                    </MudText>

                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Class="mb-2">Step 6: Install as PWA (Optional but Recommended)</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-3">
                        Stitch works as a Progressive Web App. You can install it for a native app experience:
                    </MudText>
                    <ul class="mb-3">
                        <li><strong>Desktop (Chrome/Edge):</strong> Click the install icon in the address bar (‚äï Install)</li>
                        <li><strong>Mobile (Android):</strong> Tap the menu (‚ãÆ) ‚Üí "Add to Home screen"</li>
                        <li><strong>Mobile (iOS/Safari):</strong> Tap Share ‚Üí "Add to Home Screen"</li>
                    </ul>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Color="Color.Secondary">
                        üí° <strong>Benefits:</strong> Works offline, faster loading, dedicated app window, access from your app drawer/home screen.
                    </MudText>
